The paper deals with the distributed control problem of hybrid microgrids, which involves the coordination of multiple sources of power generation. This problem is closely related to the field of control systems (cs.SY) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses issues related to communication, such as non-identical sampling rates and communication delays, which are relevant to the fields of embedded systems (cs.ET) and performance analysis (cs.PF). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm for solving the power control problem, which involves programming language concepts such as iteration and fixed-point problems, making it relevant to the field of programming languages (cs.PL).
